Description: Handle of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Only known from Petrie's drawing in his Journal, 1884-5, p.201, 22. Probably to be equated with one of two similar pieces in the British Museum. From the same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0920.21.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0531)
